This paper presents a deep convolutional neural network for breast cancer screening exam classification, which is a computer vision task and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the training procedure and the analysis of the network's performance, which involves machine learning techniques and could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions conducting a reader study, which could be categorized under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) or medical imaging (cs.MS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of probability of malignancy predicted by a radiologist, which could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM).
